    "headerDoc": "STEP 923 — Even Perfect Number Infinitude\n  ============================================\n\n  Euler-Euclid theorem (Euler 1747, Euclid 300 BC for one direction):\n    n is an even perfect number ⟺ n = 2^(p-1) · (2^p − 1) for some\n    prime p with 2^p − 1 also prime (i.e., Mersenne prime).\n\n  Consequence: **Infinite Mersenne primes ⟺ Infinite even perfect numbers.**\n\n  Rei breadth-first sweep 2026-04-19 Part E supplement (J11).\n\n  This file uses `MersennePrimes.lean` (STEP 889) `mersenne_infinitude`\n  axiom and proves that each Mersenne prime exponent p yields an even\n  perfect number, hence ∞ Mer"
